    <abstract><wysiwyg_a><p>This generic function block reads values from the u::Lux switch.</p><p>The ULUX_IN satellite function block has to be used in combination with the ULUX_SWITCH function block.</p><p>The number of in- and outputs can be increased up to 16.</p><p>
</p><p /><p>
  </p></wysiwyg_a></abstract>
  </info>
<wysiwyg><p>
    <strong>Behaviour</strong> </p><p>This is a satellite function block bound to the ULUX_SWITCH function block via the SwitchId input.</p><p>The values accessed are addressed via ActorId (zero for switch-global data, non-zero for actor data) and an addressing string specifying a value and optionally sub and sub-sub identification. The exact meaning is out of scope of this description, so this is only a quick overwiew of possible values.</p><p>
